1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,419
Mr. Mayor,

2
00:00:04,045 --> 00:00:06,172
we keep dropping in the polls.

3
00:00:06,256 --> 00:00:09,217
I told you that it was a very bad idea
to stop supporting Charly.

4
00:00:09,300 --> 00:00:12,762
We've lost many points
from decided voters around the state.

5
00:00:12,846 --> 00:00:15,473
[shushes] Look... [chuckles]
What's wrong, little one?

6
00:00:15,557 --> 00:00:18,351
We said we weren't going to
talk about that anymore.

7
00:00:18,435 --> 00:00:20,770
No need to cry over spilled honey.

8
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:23,106
Cry over spilled milk, sir.

9
00:00:23,189 --> 00:00:26,317
And please, you need to
start supporting that kid again.

10
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:28,486
That's not possible, that's not possible.

11
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:33,283
But, you know what? What I do need
is for all of the assistants...

12
00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:39,289
I don't know, give them, uh,
a plot of land, a little truck,

13
00:00:39,372 --> 00:00:42,208
but please, make sure
they're all happy and quiet.

14
00:00:42,917 --> 00:00:44,544
- [laughs]
- Why?

15
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:48,423
[scoffs]

16
00:00:50,759 --> 00:00:51,760
Why?

17
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:57,182
THE KING OF THE MACHOS

18
00:00:57,766 --> 00:00:59,893
{\an8}- <i>Toma de referee</i>. Good.
- [Charly whispers] Legs.

19
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:03,146
{\an8}- [Ramón] Legs planted. Legs planted.
- [Charly] Ah!

20
00:01:03,229 --> 00:01:08,443
{\an8}That's judo, you use your own elasticity
to break free from your opponent.

21
00:01:08,526 --> 00:01:11,196
{\an8}- Come here, I'll show you another one.
- Yeah.

22
00:01:11,279 --> 00:01:13,865
{\an8}You come here. This one's very simple.

23
00:01:13,948 --> 00:01:17,368
{\an8}Grab your opponent's arm,
you turn, and you're in control.

24
00:01:17,452 --> 00:01:19,996
{\an8}Ah, let go! I... I got it.

25
00:01:20,997 --> 00:01:23,958
{\an8}This is useless.
I'm much weaker than León.

26
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:27,420
{\an8}You think that I can get him
into a hold like this? There's no way.

27
00:01:28,505 --> 00:01:31,508
{\an8}Well, yeah.
Maybe León is stronger than you,

28
00:01:32,509 --> 00:01:34,469
{\an8}but you're faster, bro.

29
00:01:34,552 --> 00:01:36,429
{\an8}That makes you unpredictable.

30
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:39,974
{\an8}- You have to change your attitude now. Eh?
- [sighs] Yeah.

31
00:01:40,058 --> 00:01:43,228
{\an8}I mean, you can't go into the ring
like that, all defeated.

32
00:01:43,311 --> 00:01:44,729
{\an8}Obviously you'll lose.

33
00:01:45,438 --> 00:01:47,732
{\an8}Come on, show some attitude!
Good, good, good, good!

34
00:01:47,816 --> 00:01:50,485
{\an8}- Okay. Okay. Yeah.
- Come on, you try it. Ready?

35
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:54,614
{\an8}- Like that. Like that. Like that.
- You've got it. That's it, that's it.

36
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:57,158
{\an8}- Hell yeah, that's it.
- Yeah? Hey.

37
00:01:57,242 --> 00:02:01,246
{\an8}Look, when you're facing León
and he tries to pull,

38
00:02:01,329 --> 00:02:04,499
{\an8}you're going to use his own strength
against him to take control.

39
00:02:04,582 --> 00:02:06,042
{\an8}I'll explain. Come here.

40
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:08,002
{\an8}Ready? Pull me, but pull me hard.

41
00:02:08,086 --> 00:02:11,131
{\an8}There you go. Enough.
And he can't get out, eh?

42
00:02:11,214 --> 00:02:13,383
{\an8}- Okay.
- Good. Try it.

43
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:14,384
{\an8}Yeah.

44
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:17,387
{\an8}- Face-to-face, eyes...
- Mm-hmm.

45
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:19,472
[phone ringing]

46
00:02:22,559 --> 00:02:24,018
I have to take this.

47
00:02:26,396 --> 00:02:27,397
Abi?

48
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:45,540
[lock clicks]

49
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:03,600
[chuckles]

50
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:06,394
[sighs]

51
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:09,314
Are you okay?

52
00:03:09,814 --> 00:03:11,816
My parents found out about us.

53
00:03:13,234 --> 00:03:14,652
Your dad hit you?

54
00:03:15,987 --> 00:03:19,157
Let's just say that he's not
the only Castillo with a heavy hand.

55
00:03:21,409 --> 00:03:22,410
Your mom?

56
00:03:24,495 --> 00:03:27,373
[Abi] And from what I can tell,
it was no picnic for you either.

57
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:32,253
It was my dad who spoke
with Jacobo and those guys,

58
00:03:32,837 --> 00:03:35,798
and with the mayor,
so they'd shut down your parents' hostel.

59
00:03:37,634 --> 00:03:40,303
And I thought that León was
the one behind it.

60
00:03:40,887 --> 00:03:41,888
No.

61
00:03:42,513 --> 00:03:46,726
León lives with my dad's foot on his neck,
but he's not as rough as he seems.

62
00:03:49,395 --> 00:03:52,398
Your brother is hiding
a lot of things, isn't he?

63
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:54,400
[chuckles]

64
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:05,995
What's wrong?

65
00:04:13,711 --> 00:04:16,339
Abi, our relationship
has only brought you trouble.

66
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:21,135
I think it would be best to break it off.

67
00:04:22,553 --> 00:04:23,721
No, no, Charly.

68
00:04:25,890 --> 00:04:27,392
Is that really what you want?

69
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:35,858
[sighs]

70
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:38,444
Ah, I have something for you.

71
00:04:49,372 --> 00:04:51,332
What I just gave you is a bomb,

72
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:54,002
and I don't know what will happen
to my family when it explodes.

73
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:56,587
My only hope is that León can escape

74
00:04:56,671 --> 00:05:00,174
from all the bullshit my dad's
involved in, and from this town.

75
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:38,796
[bell tolls]

76
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:42,050
WELCOME TO THE BIG EVENT
THE KING OF THE MACHOS

77
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:43,426
[Inés] Today is, without a doubt,

78
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:45,762
the most important
and exciting day of the year.

79
00:05:45,845 --> 00:05:49,223
The Cowboy Corral is filled with people
who've come from near and far

80
00:05:49,307 --> 00:05:53,061
to witness the crowning
of our next Macho King.

81
00:05:53,144 --> 00:05:56,105
It's an exciting day
here in San José de las Tunas,

82
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:58,691
perhaps the only one, in this town
where nothing ever happens.

83
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:00,651
Today, the contest to select
the winner of...

84
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:02,362
Look, there's your spot.

85
00:06:02,445 --> 00:06:03,446
Come on.

86
00:06:05,823 --> 00:06:08,201
- [Alonso] Good day.
- How are you? [chuckles]

87
00:06:08,284 --> 00:06:09,827
- [Alonso] Welcome.
- How are you?

88
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:11,579
- I'll see you later, Grandpa.
- Good afternoon.

89
00:06:11,662 --> 00:06:12,663
That way.

90
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:15,166
[Inés] Good luck, Charly.

91
00:06:15,917 --> 00:06:20,296
Mr. Mayor, it's so good to see you here,
especially with how busy you are.

92
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:23,508
Look, I just wanted to thank you
for all your support.

93
00:06:23,591 --> 00:06:27,178
You've helped me much more
than you realize, eh? [chuckles]

94
00:06:28,846 --> 00:06:29,847
Charly.

95
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:32,558
Thanks.

96
00:06:43,569 --> 00:06:45,696
I'm going for a bottle opener, eh?

97
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:50,701
Afternoon.
Do you have a bottle opener, please?

98
00:06:50,785 --> 00:06:52,328
Yep, that's the one.

99
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:55,498
- Now...
- Good afternoon, sir.

100
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:58,209
Good afternoon, miss.

101
00:06:58,709 --> 00:07:00,253
A pleasure. Pepe Tejeda.

102
00:07:00,336 --> 00:07:04,382
My pleasure. Fidelia, but call me Fides.

103
00:07:04,465 --> 00:07:09,303
What a musical name.
Fides, Fidelia, like the opera.

104
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:12,223
Oh, my, how did you know that's my name?

105
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:14,267
What's my name?

106
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:17,812
Ah, Pepe Tejeda. A pleasure.
Your servant and friend, eh?

107
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:21,524
Fidelia, my pleasure, but call me Fides.

108
00:07:21,607 --> 00:07:23,443
- Fides, Fidelia.
- Mm-hmm.

109
00:07:23,526 --> 00:07:25,153
Would you like a little drink?

110
00:07:25,236 --> 00:07:26,362
Sure.

111
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:28,281
A glass for the little lady, please.

112
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:30,283
You're going to love this.

113
00:07:30,366 --> 00:07:31,742
- It's all vitamins, you'll see.
- Thanks.

114
00:07:31,826 --> 00:07:33,035
It keeps me looking great.

115
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:35,037
From the start, show her who's boss,

116
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:37,790
and go for broke with that fucking broad,
dude. No mercy.

117
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,460
- Ooh, ooh, ooh!
- Ooh, ooh, ooh!

118
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:41,752
[friend] Good, dude.

119
00:07:41,836 --> 00:07:44,297
You just focus
and use his attacks against him.

120
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:46,757
Remember, skill is better than strength.

121
00:07:47,341 --> 00:07:49,760
And you've got more than enough,
little brother. [chuckles]

122
00:07:55,099 --> 00:07:56,309
Hey, focus.

123
00:07:58,227 --> 00:07:59,353
Let's go.

124
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:08,905
Hope you're having a very good afternoon,
dear residents of Tunas and visitors.

125
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:11,908
Today is a crucial and iconic day
for everyone.

126
00:08:11,991 --> 00:08:14,952
The grand finale is about to start!

127
00:08:15,036 --> 00:08:17,371
[cheering, whistling]

128
00:08:17,455 --> 00:08:20,374
The great battle that
we've awaited for weeks:

129
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:25,588
the final duel between
Charly Tejeda and León Castillo.

130
00:08:25,671 --> 00:08:29,425
Let the competitors come in!
And let's hear it for your macho.

131
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:31,385
THE FINAL TEST
MACHO DUEL

132
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:37,683
A brutal fight, hand-to-hand combat,
sweat-to-sweat.

133
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:40,394
[spectators cheering]

134
00:08:43,898 --> 00:08:47,818
[chanting] Evil will not triumph,
evil will not triumph!

135
00:08:47,902 --> 00:08:52,448
[chanting] Charly, Charly, Charly!

136
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:54,283
Fight tough! Finish her, my boy!

137
00:08:54,909 --> 00:08:56,244
Bravo, son!

138
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:59,872
[Antonia] Tempers are running hot,
and you know why?

139
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:00,957
- Why?
- Why?

140
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:04,210
Because people know that
we're about to make history!

141
00:09:04,293 --> 00:09:06,587
- That's right! Go, Charly, go!
- Don't go anywhere, folks.

142
00:09:06,671 --> 00:09:07,505
Attaboy!

143
00:09:07,588 --> 00:09:08,673
{\an8}LEÓN is the BEST!

144
00:09:08,756 --> 00:09:10,508
{\an8}- Go, Charly!
- [Joel] Round one!

145
00:09:11,259 --> 00:09:12,468
[bell rings]

146
00:09:14,762 --> 00:09:17,265
- [friend] Focus. Focus.
- [Ramón] Go, Charly! You've got this, bro.

147
00:09:18,432 --> 00:09:19,433
Good!

148
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:27,066
[friend] Break him, asshole!
You've got it!

149
00:09:27,149 --> 00:09:28,818
[Ramón] You've got him, don't let go!

150
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:30,236
Go, Charly! Good!

151
00:09:30,319 --> 00:09:32,238
- He's back up! That's it!
- Go, Charly!

152
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:36,242
- [Ramón] There it is! That's it!
- [friend] León, pressure.

153
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:39,537
[friend speaks indistinctly]

154
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:41,372
You've got it, you've got it! There!

155
00:09:41,455 --> 00:09:44,125
Squeeze her, squeeze her!
You've got it. Come on, León.

156
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:45,668
[Ramón] Nothing, nothing.

157
00:09:46,294 --> 00:09:47,336
That's it!

158
00:09:47,962 --> 00:09:48,963
You've got it.

159
00:09:50,881 --> 00:09:54,343
She's tired, she's tired, León!
Now's the time! Let's go!

160
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:55,553
Great, León!

161
00:09:55,636 --> 00:09:58,306
[both straining]

162
00:09:59,515 --> 00:10:01,142
Underneath, underneath, dude!

163
00:10:01,225 --> 00:10:02,435
[Ramón] Come on!

164
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:05,438
You've got it! There, you've got him.

165
00:10:05,521 --> 00:10:07,440
- Hey.
- [Charly groans, yells]

166
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:10,067
- Hey, what about that stomp?
- [friend] Good, dude! Good!

167
00:10:10,151 --> 00:10:11,444
That's it! Hell yeah, assholes.

168
00:10:11,527 --> 00:10:12,862
That's it! Good.

169
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:15,281
[Joel]
And the winner of this round is León...

170
00:10:15,364 --> 00:10:18,534
- Bravo!
- ...with a super hold.

171
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:20,620
- Good.
- [bell ringing]

172
00:10:24,373 --> 00:10:25,916
- [horn blares]
- León Castillo!

173
00:10:26,834 --> 00:10:28,878
- Let's go! [chuckles]
- León, León, León!

174
00:10:28,961 --> 00:10:31,505
Come here. How are you feeling?

175
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:32,798
- Good.
- Really?

176
00:10:34,842 --> 00:10:36,052
[Ramón sighs]

177
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:38,929
Charly, you have to focus.

178
00:10:39,013 --> 00:10:41,641
You know what to do
if things get ugly. Mmm?

179
00:10:42,183 --> 00:10:43,392
How are you feeling?

180
00:10:44,143 --> 00:10:46,729
- I'm fine.
- Come on. Come on.

181
00:10:46,812 --> 00:10:47,813
You can do this.

182
00:10:49,857 --> 00:10:52,068
[Joel] Round two!

183
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:54,195
- [bell rings]
- Come on, Charly, it's your turn!

184
00:10:54,695 --> 00:10:55,863
[referee] Round two.

185
00:10:55,946 --> 00:10:57,657
- [Joel] León looks confident...
- [whistle blows]

186
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:59,950
...with the advantage he's carrying
from the first round.

187
00:11:00,993 --> 00:11:03,287
[Ramón] Come on, Charly, come on, come on!

188
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,125
[Lázaro] And pay attention
to what you're doing!

189
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:09,960
[friend] There you go, León, good.

190
00:11:10,044 --> 00:11:11,921
Tire her out, tire her out, León!

191
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:13,839
[Ramón] That's it,
don't give in, don't give in!

192
00:11:13,923 --> 00:11:16,258
[friend] Squeeze tight, dude.
You have to squeeze.

193
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:19,136
Come on, León.

194
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:21,263
[Ramón] Good, do it again!

195
00:11:22,264 --> 00:11:24,892
- [Antonia] Come on, Charly! You can do it!
- Charly, be strong!

196
00:11:24,975 --> 00:11:27,061
[Ramón] Hey, it's okay.
Get up, get up, get up!

197
00:11:27,144 --> 00:11:30,189
Stop toying with her and finish her off,
knock her down!

198
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:33,776
[Ramón] Focus! That'll work, there it is.

199
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:35,778
[friend] Pressure, pressure. Good!

200
00:11:36,529 --> 00:11:37,738
No, no, no!

201
00:11:37,822 --> 00:11:39,365
Get lower. Cover yourself.

202
00:11:39,448 --> 00:11:41,283
- Here, squeeze the elbow!
- [groans]

203
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:42,576
[Ramón] Good! Come on.

204
00:11:43,994 --> 00:11:45,413
Once more, once more.

205
00:11:45,913 --> 00:11:49,291
Show me that you're not
as big a dumbass as you look, damn it!

206
00:11:52,878 --> 00:11:54,714
- [friend] No, no, León!
- [Ramón] That's it!

207
00:11:55,297 --> 00:11:56,716
[Charly yells]

208
00:11:58,467 --> 00:12:00,469
- Fuck yeah!
- That's it!

209
00:12:00,553 --> 00:12:02,596
- [bell ringing]
- [Marquito] Go, Charly!

210
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,473
- Good!
- [Estela cheers]

211
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:06,851
- [laughs]
- [Charly] That's it!

212
00:12:06,934 --> 00:12:08,477
That's my granddaughter's boyfriend.

213
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:09,603
[Antonia] Go, Charly!

214
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:12,857
- [Estela] Let's go!
- Let's go, Charly!

215
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:14,024
- Charly Tejeda!
- [horn blares]

216
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:15,151
[Charly] Yeah!

217
00:12:16,736 --> 00:12:18,154
Go, Charly!

218
00:12:24,034 --> 00:12:25,077
[in English] Then back.

219
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:26,996
[in Spanish] We're not supporting
Charly anymore, eh?

220
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:29,498
- Why not?
- Shh. I'll tell you later.

221
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:33,711
- León, León, León!
- Charly, Charly, Charly!

222
00:12:33,794 --> 00:12:38,883
León, León, León, León, León!

223
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:47,016
[Joel] We're seeing incredible things
in today's match.

224
00:12:47,099 --> 00:12:52,062
The participant who wins this round
will be crowned for all eternity

225
00:12:52,146 --> 00:12:58,819
{\an8}as the machoest macho of all the machos
in San José de las Tunas.

226
00:12:58,903 --> 00:12:59,737
[exclaims]

227
00:13:00,571 --> 00:13:03,032
Round three!

228
00:13:03,115 --> 00:13:04,700
- [bell rings]
- [Miriam] Come on!

229
00:13:05,659 --> 00:13:07,161
If he doesn't win, I'll kill him.

230
00:13:08,788 --> 00:13:10,706
Finish off Charlota, asshole.

231
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:13,083
Don't be fooled
by that witch's tricks, dude.

232
00:13:14,084 --> 00:13:15,961
Ready to checkmate those Castillos?

233
00:13:16,045 --> 00:13:17,129
Come on, dog.

234
00:13:17,213 --> 00:13:18,714
Come on. Stay strong.

235
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:20,299
[referee] Fighters, to the ring.

236
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:27,389
Round three.

237
00:13:28,432 --> 00:13:29,433
