Oh, Doloritas, my <i>comadre</i>,
what a disgrace our town has become!

469
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:46,896
Oh, my <i>comadre</i>, with so much revolution,
honestly, I've realized a few things

470
00:26:48,273 --> 00:26:50,025
and I have to tell you something.

471
00:27:00,994 --> 00:27:02,287
[Pepe] I'd like you to meet Charly,

472
00:27:02,370 --> 00:27:04,914
he's my grandson
and we're very proud of him.

473
00:27:04,998 --> 00:27:08,460
Nice to meet you, son. Congratulations.

474
00:27:08,543 --> 00:27:10,545
[chuckles] Nice to meet you, ma'am.

475
00:27:15,842 --> 00:27:16,843
Thanks, Grandpa.

476
00:27:18,803 --> 00:27:19,804
[sighs]

477
00:27:21,056 --> 00:27:23,224
Never come down from the clouds, okay?

478
00:27:30,523 --> 00:27:31,524
We'll miss you.

479
00:27:32,108 --> 00:27:34,027
And I'll miss you, dear Marquito.

480
00:27:34,694 --> 00:27:35,904
[chuckles]

481
00:27:39,282 --> 00:27:40,492
[both chuckle]

482
00:27:40,575 --> 00:27:42,535
Wow, it's so hot, isn't it? [sniffles]

483
00:27:42,619 --> 00:27:44,704
- Even my eyes are sweating.
- [chuckles]

484
00:27:44,788 --> 00:27:46,206
SAN JOSÉ DE LAS TUNAS
BUS STATION

485
00:27:46,289 --> 00:27:47,290
It's okay.

486
00:27:55,382 --> 00:27:56,591
[Charly sniffles]

487
00:27:58,551 --> 00:28:00,053
You sure you won't come with me?

488
00:28:00,136 --> 00:28:02,764
With the sale of the tractor,
we can see what happens, or not.

489
00:28:02,847 --> 00:28:04,683
No, no, no, I don't know, just wait.

490
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:06,810
I need my time.

491
00:28:07,727 --> 00:28:12,190
Besides, you and I will always be together
in some way or another. Right?

492
00:28:12,691 --> 00:28:16,403
Or did you think
you could get rid of me so easily?

493
00:28:16,486 --> 00:28:18,780
[chuckles, sniffles] I know I can't.

494
00:28:18,863 --> 00:28:19,864
No.

495
00:28:21,991 --> 00:28:22,992
[Charly sobs]

496
00:28:28,164 --> 00:28:29,374
I love you, Antonia.

497
00:28:31,793 --> 00:28:33,211
Love you too.

498
00:28:33,294 --> 00:28:34,379
With my whole heart.

499
00:28:53,273 --> 00:28:55,275
Are you sure you have to go, son?

500
00:28:57,902 --> 00:28:59,070
Yes, Mom.

501
00:29:01,448 --> 00:29:03,283
I'm going to miss you a ton.

502
00:29:04,033 --> 00:29:06,369
But I can't stay in this town.

503
00:29:07,704 --> 00:29:12,584
[Alonso] Remember that
whenever you need us, we'll be here.

504
00:29:20,592 --> 00:29:24,179
You know that I couldn't have
done it without you, right?

505
00:29:27,098 --> 00:29:28,308
[Charly cries]

506
00:29:31,436 --> 00:29:33,396
- [laughs]
- [Estela chuckles]

507
00:29:34,105 --> 00:29:35,398
[Charly] It looks like me.

508
00:29:35,482 --> 00:29:36,483
[chuckles]

509
00:29:51,331 --> 00:29:52,957
[bus engine starts]

510
00:29:53,958 --> 00:29:55,585
- Bye, Charly.
- [Charly chuckles] Bye.

511
00:29:55,668 --> 00:29:57,003
[Estela] Bye.

512
00:29:57,086 --> 00:29:58,213
[Pepe] Attaboy, Charly.

513
00:29:58,296 --> 00:29:59,297
[door closes]

514
00:31:36,144 --> 00:31:38,146
Translated by Catharine Lailson

